			<h2>About COMPUTERBILD Safer surf 2009</h2>
			<h3>License and trademarks</h3>
			<p>
			COMPUTERBILD Safer surf uses many software components that are subject to
			the GNU General Public license. Because of the limited space on this disc it is not
			possible to include the source code on CD. You may order source code and used patches 
			from the developer Mattias Schlenker directly 
			(email: <a href="mailto:gpl@lesslinux.org">gpl@lesslinux.org</a>).
			</p>
			<p>
			If you are interested in the technical backgrounds and the architecture of the system,
			you should take a look at <a href="http://www.lesslinux.org/">www.lesslinux.org</a> 
			or the development blog <a href="http://blog.lesslinux.org/">blog.lesslinux.org</a>.
			There you can download versions of the source code and the build scripts that <i>do not
			use trademarks from Axel Springer AG</i>. These might be used as base for own modifications.
			</p>
